description:
The Computer Science program at Oxford University offers a cutting-edge curriculum focusing on
                    theoretical foundations and practical applications. Students benefit from world-class
                    faculty, state-of-the-art research facilities, and strong industry connections.
                    The program emphasizes foundational skills
                    and prepares graduates for successful careers.

                    Entry requirements: High school diploma with strong grades in relevant subjects.

                    Career prospects: Graduates typically find positions in entry to mid-level positions across various industries.

The Computer Science program at Oxford University offers a cutting-edge curriculum focusing on
                    theoretical foundations and practical applications. Students benefit from world-class
                    faculty, state-of-the-art research facilities, and strong industry connections.
                    The program emphasizes research methodology
                    and prepares graduates for advanced research or industry leadership.

                    Entry requirements: Bachelor degree with 2:1 or equivalent, relevant experience preferred.

                    Career prospects: Graduates typically find positions in senior roles at tech companies, research institutions, or pursue PhD studies.
